steps.step: {"blocks":[{"key":"7b40i","text":"Add 400 mL DNA extraction solution into   centrifuge tube.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[{"key":0,"offset":40,"length":1}],"data":{}},{"key":"4cgta","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{"0":{"type":"amount","mutability":"MUTABLE","data":{"amount":"1.5","error":false,"guid":"A92F2BC08CBA11EDA3091175E0EC6004","id":0,"label":"","scientificNotation":false,"unit":2}}}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"4g2lo","text":"Grind 3 small leaves or 1 large leaf with a grinding stick in the centrifuge tube with the extract.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"6kpe5","text":"Shake the oscillator for  , and place it at room temperature until other preparations are completed.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[{"key":0,"offset":25,"length":1}],"data":{}},{"key":"1jbgg","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{"0":{"type":"duration","mutability":"MUTABLE","data":{"duration":5,"guid":"B573BC208CBA11EDA3091175E0EC6004","id":0,"label":"","pause":null,"preset":[],"start":null}}}}
{"blocks":[{"key":"bebd8","text":"Centrifuge at 16 000 rpm for 2 minutes at room temperature.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"8u5v1","text":"Transfer 200 mL of centrifuged supernatant into a clean centrifuge tube.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"3qsko","text":"Add 200 mL isopropanol, mix well and place at room temperature for 3 minutes.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"22m08","text":"Centrifuge at 16 000 rpm at room temperature for 5 minutes, remove the supernatant, wash the precipitate with 70% ethanol, and dry the precipitate at room temperature.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"b65ln","text":"Dissolve DNA in 100 mL deionized water and store it in a refrigerator at – 20 ° C.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}
